      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Dawat E Islami USA demonstrates a unique operational model where administrative and fundraising costs are virtually non-existent in public filings. The organization reported <cite id=\"10\">$2,429,214 in revenue</cite> while maintaining a <cite id=\"11\">96.4% independent board</cite>, which provides strong oversight for its financial activities. Their impact is quantified through high-volume educational outputs, such as <cite id=\"12\">multiple booklet titles published</cite> and extensive <cite id=\"13\">Quranic recitation programs</cite>. This combination of fiscal discipline and specialized religious focus allows them to serve as a primary resource for Islamic education across <cite id=\"14\">multiple countries including the USA, UK, and Pakistan</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "Dawat E Islami USA Inc is a long-standing religious and educational institution that has been <cite id=\"1\">operating since 1981</cite> to preserve Islamic cultural values. The organization manages a diverse portfolio of programs including <cite id=\"2\">Quranic memorization (Hifz), Aalim courses, and mosque construction</cite>. Financially, the charity operates with extreme efficiency, reporting a <cite id=\"3\">96.4% program expense ratio</cite> in its most recent filings. This means every dollar of revenue is directed toward its core mission of religious education and community services. The organization reported <cite id=\"4\">$2,429,214 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year, primarily driven by <cite id=\"5\">$2.4 million in public contributions</cite>. Beyond education, the charity facilitates spiritual growth through specialized activities like <cite id=\"6\">I'tikaf programs at 29 locations</cite> and the publication of religious literature. Its financial model is notably lean, achieving <cite id=\"7\">fundraising efficiency of $0.00 per $1 raised</cite>, which is rare even among high-performing non-profits. This efficiency is supported by a strong liquidity position, maintaining <cite id=\"8\">20.2 months of working capital</cite> to ensure program continuity during economic fluctuations.",
